2004: A strong earthquake off the west coast of Aceh province in northern Sumatra, Indonesia, triggered a tsunami on December 26, affecting 14 countries and killing 226,000 people in the coastal areas of the Indian Ocean, almost half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of severe earthquakes hit the west coast of Sumatra between late March and early April.
