2006: A 6.8 magnitude earthquake shook southern Java, Indonesia's most populous island, triggering a tsunami that hit the southern coast and killed nearly 700 people.
2009: A 7.6 magnitude earthquake hit the city of Padang, the capital of West Sumatra Province.
