2010: A 7.5 magnitude earthquake shook one of the Mentawai Islands off Sumatra, triggering a tsunami as high as 10 meters (33 feet) high, destroying dozens of villages and claiming some 300 lives.
2016: A minor earthquake shook the Pidie Jaya government district in Aceh, causing destruction and panic as people were reminded of the devastation of the deadly 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
